        &ldquo;Sharing a successful partnership for more than a decade. A great local company that provides products and services with a smile.&rdquo;
        <cite>Kawartha Dairy &mdash; Est. 1937, Ontario</cite>
      </blockquote>
      <div class="lp-quote-strip__logo">
        {%- if section.settings.testimonial_logo != blank -%}
          {{ section.settings.testimonial_logo | image_url: width: 300 | image_tag: loading: 'lazy', alt: 'Kawartha Dairy', height: 48 }}
        {%- endif -%}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {%- comment -%}FAQ{%- endcomment -%}
  <section class="lp-faq" aria-label="Frequently asked questions">
    <div class="lp-faq__inner">
      <div class="lp-faq__head">
        <p class="lp-faq__eyebrow bbi-mono">Common questions</p>
        <h2>What school boards and colleges ask before sending the PO.</h2>
        <p class="lp-faq__cta">Still have a question? <a href="tel:18008359565">Call 1-800-835-9565</a> or <a href="/pages/quote">request a quote</a> and we&rsquo;ll respond in 1 business day.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="lp-faq__list">

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">01</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">Can Ontario school boards purchase under OECM without a tender?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>Yes. Brant Business Interiors is an OECM Supplier Partner (Agreement 2025-470). Ontario school boards, district school boards, and colleges can purchase directly without an open tender or RFP. We include the agreement number on every quote. If you&rsquo;re unsure whether your board qualifies, call us &mdash; we&rsquo;ll confirm in five minutes.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">02</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">What are the lead times for large institutional orders?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>Lead times depend on product and quantity. In-stock items ship in 2&ndash;4 weeks. Custom or made-to-order pieces typically run 8&ndash;12 weeks. We flag lead times on the quote so you can plan around the school calendar. For renovation-season orders (June&ndash;August), we recommend submitting by April to secure your window.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">03</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">Do you accept purchase orders and NET 30?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>Yes &mdash; school boards and post-secondary institutions can pay by purchase order with NET 30 terms. We issue a formal quote, you issue a PO, and we bill on delivery. For OECM orders, the agreement number appears on the quote so your finance team can process it without additional procurement paperwork.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">04</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">Is the space plan included in the quote, or is it a separate fee?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>Included &mdash; no extra fee. Send us your floor plan (PDF, sketch, or AutoCAD file) and we&rsquo;ll place the furniture and show you a layout before you approve anything. This applies to every room type: admin offices, staff rooms, boardrooms, and training rooms.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">05</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">Can you phase delivery around an occupied school schedule?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>Yes. We coordinate delivery around the school calendar and offer phased delivery windows for multi-room projects. For occupied buildings, we can deliver and install room by room to minimize disruption. Early morning and weekend delivery is available at most Ontario locations. We plan the sequence with your facilities team before the first truck arrives.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {%- comment -%}CTA CLOSER{%- endcomment -%}
